			<h4>How it’s different from hiring</h4>
			<h2>A senior technology partner without the cost of a full-time CTO</h2>

			<p>A full-time CTO is a £150k-plus commitment, six months of hiring, and a relationship you can’t easily unwind if it doesn’t work. For a lot of growing businesses that’s the wrong shape.</p>

			<p><strong>Faster to start.</strong> We can be in conversation with you next week, not next quarter. No agency, no notice period, no onboarding overhead.</p>

			<p><strong>More senior than you could afford full-time.</strong> Twenty-plus years of experience, applied where it counts – without the salary, equity, and on-cost of a permanent hire.</p>

			<p><strong>Independent.</strong> No internal politics. No career angles. We’ll tell you what we’d do if it were our own money on the line.</p>

			<p><strong>Knowledge transfer, not dependency.</strong> Our job is to make you better at the technology calls, not to lock you into needing us forever. When the engagement ends, you keep what we’ve built and what we’ve taught you.</p>

			<p><strong>Scales with you.</strong> Buy more time when you’re making big decisions, less when things are steady. Nothing renews automatically.</p>

